      "span_text": "For the second method, indium chloride is dissolved in acetonitrile and ethylene glycol (v: v = 50:1). The precursor was stirred at 50 ºC for 2 hours then spin coated on cleaned substrates at 5000 rpm followed by pre-annealing at 100 ºC for 5 min on hotplate, then annealing at 500 ºC for 1 hour in furnace."
